<h3>Book Reviews*</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Philosophy-Shame-Revolutionary-Emotion/dp/1804294152?crid=28PSIW3T871UC&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.P5XY9ewrR_DFzxs2m0uPFg._qUfiObTUW66bHu6OhfHnQk21lduYH5JFo4dzOdupyw&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=philosophy+of+shame+Fr%C3%A9d%C3%A9ric+Gros&amp;qid=1747654257&amp;sprefix=philosophy+of+shame+fr%C3%A9d%C3%A9ric+gros%2Caps%2C79&amp;sr=8-1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=541520f9810751d180ea7c1c48e86536&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>A Philosophy of Shame: A Revolutionary Emotion</em></a> by Frédéric Gros is reviewed by Nina Power at <a href="https://www.telegraph.co.uk/books/non-fiction/review-a-philosophy-of-shame-frederic-gros/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Telegraph</em></a>.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Also-History-Philosophy-Occidental-Constellation/dp/1509545174?crid=1J5O09TYYHCH2&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9._CPgHkguZeO-jDtWT1crMg.HUwHSrXEyGGuyOvxX12uLR6WbYN4MKk_P5KilY9ZQv0&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=History+of+Philosophy%2C+Vol.+II%3A+The+Occidental+Constellation+of+Faith+and+Knowledge&amp;qid=1747653074&amp;sprefix=history+of+philosophy%2C+vol.+ii+the+occidental+constellation+of+faith+and+knowledge%2Caps%2C76&amp;sr=8-1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=fb2c809b7d550c9abda99feb77151898&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Also a History of Philosophy, Vol. II: The Occidental Constellation of Faith and Knowledge</em></a> by Jürgen Habermas, translated by Ciaran Cronin is reviewed by Martin Jay at <a href="https://ndpr.nd.edu/reviews/also-a-history-of-philosophy-vol-ii-the-occidental-constellation-of-faith-and-knowledge/"><em>Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews</em></a><em>.</em></li>
<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Varieties-Voluntarism-Medieval-Modern-Philosophy/dp/1032291060?crid=1HZ4POF530CG2&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.pDj5ikI8720_ZqDlHfljkg.v4_iTQ5l9CntuX1AUDQjuDl-fqbuLyK4qeyhUdNwBWE&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Varieties+of+Voluntarism+In+Medieval+and+Early+Modern+Philosophy&amp;qid=1747653030&amp;sprefix=varieties+of+voluntarism+in+medieval+and+early+modern+philosophy%2Caps%2C97&amp;sr=8-1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=f240889312266edab13bdb79bce7dc6e&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Varieties of Voluntarism In Medieval and Early Modern Philosophy </em></a>by Jörn Müller and Sonja Schierbaum (eds.) is reviewed by Monika Michałowska at <a href="https://ndpr.nd.edu/reviews/varieties-of-voluntarism-in-medieval-and-early-modern-philosophy/"><em>Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews</em></a>.</li>
<li><em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Plato-Tyrant-Greatest-Philosophic-Masterpiece/dp/1324093188?crid=3E3MXYWA49BTT&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.wOqjLg6MoI8ibGgQrii1ag.HQkpQ1qLkU2l4bfAI7VQXs3TDv73VvK4LDx_JZVXD00&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Plato+and+the+Tyrant%3A+The+Fall+of+Greece%27s+Greatest+Dynasty+and+the+Making+of+a+Philosophic+Masterpiece&amp;qid=1747653699&amp;sprefix=plato+and+the+tyrant+the+fall+of+greece%27s+greatest+dynasty+and+the+making+of+a+philosophic+masterpiece%2Caps%2C143&amp;sr=8-1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=a47f756134631e154b5712443a128318&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plato and the Tyrant: The Fall of Greece&#8217;s Greatest Dynasty and the Making of a Philosophic Masterpiece</a> </em>by James Romm is reviewed at <a href="https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/james-romm/plato-and-the-tyrant/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Kirkus</em></a>.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Arguing-Better-World-issues-divide/dp/1529390575?_encoding=UTF8&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.DUsUQkhT6nOk0qbMjBy66g.9oELgu-YkxdD0fuQ893_bW2Mjb_uHKWH6lO0498LEe0&amp;qid=1747655916&amp;sr=8-1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=dainou-20&amp;linkId=ef6ae623248053704ec8502933519ba9&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Arguing for a Better World: How to Talk about the Issues that Divide Us</em></a> by Arianne Shahvisi is reviewed by Alan Sokal at <a href="https://thecritic.co.uk/how-not-to-argue/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Critic</em></a>.</li>
